Method Detail

process

public static void process(java.lang.Object object,
                           java.util.Properties... properties)
This method is an entry point to the parser logic.
Any object or class that have Property annotation in it or it's parent class/interface can be submitted here.
If object(new Something()) is submitted, object fields are parsed. (non-static)
If class is submitted(Sotmething.class), static fields are parsed.

Parameters:
object - Class or Object that has Property annotations.
properties - Properties that should be used while seraching for a Property.key()

process

processFields

private static void processFields(java.lang.Class clazz,
                                  java.lang.Object obj,
                                  java.util.Properties[] props)
This method runs throught the declared fields watching for the Property annotation. It also watches for the field modifiers like Modifier.STATIC and Modifier.FINAL

Parameters:
clazz - Class of object
obj - Object if any, null if parsing class (static fields only)
props - Properties with keys\values

processField

private static void processField(java.lang.reflect.Field f,
                                 java.lang.Object obj,
                                 java.util.Properties[] props)
This method takes Property annotation and does sets value according to annotation property. For this reason getFieldValue(java.lang.reflect.Field, java.util.Properties[]) can be called, however if method sees that there is no need - field can remain with it's initial value.

Also this method is capturing and logging all Exception that are thrown by underlying methods.

Parameters:
f - field that is going to be processed
obj - Object if any, null if parsing class (static fields only)
props - Properties with kyes\values

getFieldValue

private static java.lang.Object getFieldValue(java.lang.reflect.Field field,
                                              java.util.Properties[] props)
                                       throws TransformationException
This method is responsible for receiving field value.
It tries to load property by key, if not found - it uses default value.
Transformation is done using PropertyTransformerFactory

Parameters:
field - field that has to be transformed
props - properties with key\values
Returns:
transformed object that will be used as field value
Throws:
TransformationException - if something goes wrong during transformation
